Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.10,0:00:06.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Encounters are mysterious!\NBut Osaka is even more so!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.37,0:00:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad I'm with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.27,0:00:10.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today is a 60-minute Naniwa special
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.01,0:00:12.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,filled with incidents and mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.14,0:00:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.65,0:00:15.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and looks like a kid but\Nhas the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.48,0:00:18.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.45,0:00:26.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I spun the roulette of destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.19,0:00:33.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and always watched you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.13,0:00:41.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is it that I'm this happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.34,0:00:48.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,yet I feel sad when I look at the horizon?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.81,0:01:01.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's as if I'm looking at\Nmyself back then, from afar
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.29,0:01:09.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Spin the roulette of destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.47,0:01:15.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking too hard about\Nthis and that is a mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.31,0:01:21.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? The person of\Nyour destiny is right there,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.81,0:01:28.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,watching you always
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.30,0:01:45.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim is Okazaki Sumie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, age 39.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.04,0:01:48.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was strangled to\Ndeath with a rope of some sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.24,0:01:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She appears to have been\Nstabbed after being strangled.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.78,0:01:54.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What time did you find the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.65,0:01:57.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three or four minutes before you arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.82,0:02:00.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This bathroom cleaner guy found her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.92,0:02:06.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why does the killer\Nstab their wallets every time?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.26,0:02:12.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You told this lady not to go outside,\Nbut it looks like she died here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.76,0:02:18.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to the Shinsai Bridge now if\Nyou want to see some old friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.80,0:02:23.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,1:08 pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.38,0:02:28.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See that? You're the next to wind up like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.65,0:02:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,1:10 pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.78,0:02:35.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no question that's the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.69,0:02:39.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the lady\Nheard the first message
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.69,0:02:41.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and went to the Shinsai Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.59,0:02:44.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, when she came back,\Nshe heard the second message
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.93,0:02:47.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and trembled in fear inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.77,0:02:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what does "old friends" mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.44,0:02:56.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it refer to the people\Nwho've been killed so far?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.91,0:02:59.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Sakata.\NThere's a call from headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.48,0:03:01.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.05,0:03:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Hattori. These answering\Nmachine messages are strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.25,0:03:06.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.62,0:03:09.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The times and the contents of the messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.52,0:03:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were only two minutes\Nbetween the "come" message
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.06,0:03:16.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the "see that" message.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.90,0:03:21.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does that mean the killer was watching her?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.30,0:03:25.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something's odd about these four murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.50,0:03:30.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get a bad feeling that the\Nkiller is playing with us...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.08,0:03:31.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bad feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.72,0:03:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.65,0:03:41.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.05,0:03:43.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-Nothing! Don't sweat it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.89,0:03:48.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yikes! I Just remembered that\Nominous dream from the other day!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.17,0:03:56.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. Where to next?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.97,0:04:00.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shall we visit Goshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s office?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.61,0:04:03.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.91,0:04:05.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.94,0:04:08.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These sure are strange cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.65,0:04:12.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are no witnesses and it's\Nnot clear how they're all connected,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.38,0:04:14.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,yet we can ID the victims easily enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.85,0:04:16.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, now that you mention it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.62,0:04:22.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victims' names were on the\Nnews right after the first two killings.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.33,0:04:24.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's only natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.46,0:04:29.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All four had their driver's\Nlicenses in their stabbed wallets.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.20,0:04:31.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Driver's licenses? That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.80,0:04:34.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Kadoma Driver's License Testing Ground"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.67,0:04:37.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So all four have clean driving records...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.41,0:04:38.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.34,0:04:43.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought there might be a car\Nconnection. Guess I was wrong again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.48,0:04:49.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They also all got their licenses\Ndifferent years at different places.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.25,0:04:54.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey. It says Okazaki learned to\Ndrive in Hyogo and not Osaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.63,0:04:56.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.03,0:04:58.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why that far away?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.66,0:05:03.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that place is famous for\Nits cheap license school.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.03,0:05:06.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,License school?! Does that mean...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.37,0:05:09.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...lf you want to see some old friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.11,0:05:11.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's her friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.64,0:05:14.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have the number for that place, Mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.68,0:05:16.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.85,0:05:22.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okazaki Sumie and Nishiguchi Tayo\Nshared a room at the school?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.85,0:05:24.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.19,0:05:28.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright! We're starting to\Nconnect the four victims now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.29,0:05:31.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But... isn't it strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.40,0:05:35.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got her license that same year,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.00,0:05:39.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but Nishiguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got his three years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.40,0:05:44.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he sucked at driving\Nand didn't graduate that year?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.01,0:05:47.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.01,0:05:49.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're really sure about that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.31,0:05:51.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?! What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.48,0:05:57.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The others were at that\Nschool 20 years ago, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.02,0:06:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first victim, Nagao Hidetoshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.66,0:06:04.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the third victim, Noyasu Kazuto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.16,0:06:09.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Assemblyman Goshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.67,0:06:13.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were all at the same place!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.04,0:06:14.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.47,0:06:17.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.18,0:06:21.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was also a man whose\Nname is all too familiar now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.95,0:06:25.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Familiar?! Who?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.98,0:06:29.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Numabuchi. Numabuchi Kiichiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.72,0:06:33.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Numabuchi Kiichiro? You don't mean...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.26,0:06:35.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The robber and murderer...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.59,0:06:39.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...who's on the run?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.40,0:06:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here it comes! The school photo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.87,0:06:48.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No question about it! It's Numabuchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.21,0:06:51.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The faces and names of\Nthe other five match, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.28,0:06:52.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this is strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.71,0:06:53.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"August 23, 1978 graduates"\NBut this is strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.41,0:06:57.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"August 23, 1978 graduates"\NSee? It says they all graduated then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.18,0:06:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? It says they all graduated then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.65,0:07:01.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...but only Okazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nwent on to get her license.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.02,0:07:06.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something happened at this\Nschool 20 years ago. Something...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.93,0:07:10.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.03,0:07:15.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,None of the current staff know\Nanything that happened 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.03,0:07:16.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figured as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.80,0:07:20.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Prefectural Nakanoshima Library"\NBut there had to have\Nbeen some sort of incident
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.77,0:07:21.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there had to have\Nbeen some sort of incident
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.11,0:07:26.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,involving that training ground 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.51,0:07:31.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bingo! This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.18,0:07:31.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Driving Instructor Dies in Accident"\N"Drunk Driving Suspected"\NBingo! This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.92,0:07:34.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Driving Instructor Dies in Accident"\N"Drunk Driving Suspected"\NOn that day 20 years ago\Nwhen those six graduated,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.35,0:07:37.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Driving Instructor Dies in Accident"\N"Drunk Driving Suspected"\None of the instructors died\Nin a drunk driving accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.99,0:07:38.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of the instructors died\Nin a drunk driving accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.42,0:07:42.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name was Inaba Tetsuji.\NThe strictest instructor at the school...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.89,0:07:45.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, how does this sound to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.30,0:07:50.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Numabuchi, broke and in trouble,\Ndecided to use the old incident
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.47,0:07:54.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to blackmail the assemblyman\Nout of money but was refused.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.87,0:07:58.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he killed off everyone\Ninvolved in the incident
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.41,0:08:00.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then repeated his threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.58,0:08:03.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That, or Goshi used\NNumabuchi to kill off everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.58,0:08:09.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to keep the scandal from interfering\Nwith his Diet member campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.39,0:08:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both sound plausible enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.06,0:08:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Nagao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Noyasu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nquit working for him,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.49,0:08:19.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they received a lot of severance pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.76,0:08:25.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mention the instructor's death\Nand his companions back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.90,0:08:29.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and I bet that cop-hater will start talking!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.31,0:08:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.18,0:08:41.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! What are you doing here?!\NYou suddenly disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.19,0:08:43.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no! I forgot to call!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.42,0:08:46.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Hei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! Long time, no see!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.79,0:08:50.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otaki-han from headquarters?!\NWhy are you here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.40,0:08:53.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Inspector Otaki Osaka\NPrefectural Police"\NKazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} asked me to be a driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.60,0:08:54.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Inspector Otaki Osaka\NPrefectural Police"\NSakata-han called us about the glasses boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.13,0:08:57.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sakata-han called us about the glasses boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.90,0:09:00.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now why'd you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.27,0:09:03.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Must be convenient, always having\Nthe cops at your beck and call!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.54,0:09:07.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who're you to talk?! You were\Ntouring Osaka in a police car!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.55,0:09:08.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.88,0:09:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can drive the boy to the\Nchief's house if you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.02,0:09:14.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.12,0:09:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! I wanna stay with Heiji-niichan!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.22,0:09:19.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a minute, Otaki-han.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.49,0:09:28.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Osaka. Just leave this\Nto us and go on your way, Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.53,0:09:34.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But knowing you, you'll just\Nfind a way to butt in again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.81,0:09:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fine, then. I'll let you hold onto this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.51,0:09:39.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your good luck charm?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.71,0:09:43.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In exchange, hold yourself\Nback as much as you can today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.25,0:09:46.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I come home, I'll tell\Nyou all about what happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.99,0:09:48.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Kay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.42,0:09:52.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.79,0:09:59.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. I won't let\Nthem mess with Osaka anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.33,0:10:01.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet my life on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.77,0:10:03.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.94,0:10:07.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's he talking to?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.28,0:10:12.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm starving...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.48,0:10:17.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be at the chief's house\Nin Neyagawa in half an hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.45,0:10:21.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji's mom is making blowfish stew tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.69,0:10:22.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.89,0:10:25.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.26,0:10:29.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.23,0:10:30.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.23,0:10:32.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You found the car of Numabuchi, the fugitive,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.86,0:10:34.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in the Mino mountains?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.20,0:10:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.47,0:10:42.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Mori-han, but you'll have to\Nwait longer for the blowfish stew.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.31,0:10:44.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm taking a side trip!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.38,0:10:53.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Mino Waterfall"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.76,0:11:03.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry! I'll have a youngster\Ncome get you in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.70,0:11:04.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.73,0:11:08.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't Numabuchi that\Nmurderer who escaped with a gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.77,0:11:13.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Things have gotten really bad. Right, Conan...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.27,0:11:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.94,0:11:19.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- How's it look?\N- Oh, Inspector Otaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.38,0:11:25.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found the car covered in\Nplants, but Numabuchi is still...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.05,0:11:27.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that shack?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.02,0:11:29.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was empty when I peeked inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.89,0:11:34.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he ditched the car\Nand ran off somewhere else?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.09,0:11:35.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.93,0:11:39.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,L-Little boy! When did you get here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.63,0:11:41.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have a look here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.70,0:11:47.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found these burned at the bottom of this can.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.37,0:11:51.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? Convenience store receipts\Nfrom five and three days ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.58,0:11:55.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and stickers from lots of convenience\Nstore lunches that expire today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.78,0:11:58.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not many people would eat\Nconvenience store lunches
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.45,0:12:00.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,at a place like this every day, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.69,0:12:05.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, boy, if a wanted man\Nshowed up at a convenience store...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.52,0:12:08.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone else probably bought it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.33,0:12:11.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone's sheltering him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.10,0:12:13.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For some reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.44,0:12:26.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! You find Numabuchi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.81,0:12:28.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.01,0:12:32.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! There are signs that\Nsomeone lived here awhile ago, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.26,0:12:40.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's mud on the windowsill!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.23,0:12:44.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That pillar and those\Nbeams are free of cobwebs...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.60,0:12:48.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! He stood on the windowsill and...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.17,0:12:55.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Stop, little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.28,0:13:05.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh?! It looks like this leads to the attic!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.82,0:13:09.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, boy! Leave the rest to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.56,0:13:17.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Numabuchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.86,0:13:21.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Numabuchi Kiichiro! You're under\Narrest for robbery and murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.33,0:13:23.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,F-Food!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.97,0:13:26.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry, give me food!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.41,0:13:28.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Goshi Sotaro's residence"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.37,0:13:30.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Goshi Sotaro's residence"\NWhat?! Old man Goshi won't come out?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.91,0:13:31.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! Old man Goshi won't come out?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.88,0:13:36.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he's kept us waiting\Nin here since this evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.41,0:13:38.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go see him myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.45,0:13:43.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now! Please simmer down\Nand let my senior save face!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.92,0:13:44.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sir! We can't keep the police\Ndetectives waiting any longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.72,0:13:47.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Goshi Sotaro\NPrefectural Assemblyman"\NSir! We can't keep the police\Ndetectives waiting any longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.93,0:13:48.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sir! We can't keep the police\Ndetectives waiting any longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.36,0:13:52.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forget 'em. They'll give\Nup and leave eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.36,0:13:57.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shall I at least tell them about the\Nphone call with the strange voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.77,0:14:01.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No! I absolutely can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.87,0:14:07.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's make a deal in one hour\Nabout the incident 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.15,0:14:12.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go out the back gate and\Nwait in the far storehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.85,0:14:15.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We absolutely can't tell them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.12,0:14:20.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sheesh! I told you to stop\Nscampering around, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.86,0:14:23.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- All you do is worry me...\N- Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.16,0:14:26.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on! Get walking!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.70,0:14:32.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.57,0:14:37.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.88,0:14:39.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.81,0:14:41.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Outta the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.59,0:14:53.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no use!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.76,0:15:00.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.97,0:15:04.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Hang in there! Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.24,0:15:12.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.11,0:15:16.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.05,0:15:18.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.48,0:15:21.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Where's Sakata-han?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.52,0:15:24.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He just left to use the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.39,0:15:26.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should probably go, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.19,0:15:31.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.90,0:15:34.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone rush him to the hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.93,0:15:36.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.87,0:15:39.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm okay... It only pricked me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.67,0:15:42.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be! The knife went...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.25,0:15:49.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A good luck charm?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.95,0:15:54.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must be thanks to the good\Nluck charm Heiji-niichan lent me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.72,0:15:56.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji's?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.49,0:16:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? The knife got caught in the\Nchain link, so it couldn't stab me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.60,0:16:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Never do that again!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.63,0:16:08.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Up, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.87,0:16:10.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No funny business!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.50,0:16:15.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why does he have two\Nhandcuffs on his left hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.07,0:16:21.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, this? I'm not sure why, but\Nhe was handcuffed to a pillar.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.01,0:16:26.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We had to get him free, so we cut\Nthe chain and put our cuffs on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.85,0:16:28.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was handcuffed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.89,0:16:35.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like you were right about\Nsomeone bringing him food, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.99,0:16:37.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.70,0:16:40.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't be! It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.73,0:16:43.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.00,0:16:46.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.72,0:17:07.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait all you want, old man Goshi won't come.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.26,0:17:13.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sakata-han. You're the\Nserial murderer, aren't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.80,0:17:17.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,P-Please don't joke like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.07,0:17:22.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just admiring how\Nunusual this storehouse is!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.74,0:17:26.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, when the body fell onto the cop car...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.24,0:17:29.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You craftily took us there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.91,0:17:34.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mere moments before we exited\Nthe restaurant, you made a call
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.72,0:17:41.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and put the special set-up in action.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.86,0:17:47.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, while I was on the roof, you\Ncalled Okazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to the scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.80,0:17:52.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,left a threatening call on her\Nmachine when you knew she was gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.80,0:17:57.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and led her to hole up in her apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.31,0:18:02.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After you had me witness her\Nand made an impression on her,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.48,0:18:08.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you brought up the topic and called\Nher after passing her apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.69,0:18:14.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, after I heard her frightened\Nvoice and leapt from the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.39,0:18:22.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you parked the car in an alley and\Ncalled her again while chasing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.17,0:18:25.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the detective who just\Ncalled! You're in danger there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.27,0:18:29.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait in the nearby\Npublic restroom! Got it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.57,0:18:40.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, while we were in her room,\Nyou killed her in the restroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.42,0:18:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were able to arrive by car\Nimmediately after she was found
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.06,0:18:53.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because you had rented two\Ncars of the exact same model!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.76,0:18:59.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After you killed her, you got in\Nthe other rental car that was nearby
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.97,0:19:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to make it look like you'd just\Ngotten there after some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.48,0:19:12.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You drove for us and got us\Ncloser to the heart of the case
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.48,0:19:16.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to get everyone here so you\Ncould kill old man Goshi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.29,0:19:19.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a prefectural assemblyman.\NHe'd stand out if he left his home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.99,0:19:22.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he could even take bodyguards with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.96,0:19:29.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if you came here with us,\Nyou could wander around freely.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.84,0:19:33.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you did you realize it, Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.97,0:19:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rental cars' side-view\Nmirrors were the first thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.07,0:19:41.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was at a different angle the second time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.25,0:19:47.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then I noticed the instructor\Nin the picture from 20 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.65,0:19:50.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,looked a lot like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.62,0:19:54.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was your habit in the car\Nthat finally convinced me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.03,0:19:56.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You fiddled with the rear-view mirror
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.03,0:20:00.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the same way Noyasu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nand Okazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.53,0:20:04.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's proof you'd all been\Ninvolved with the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.77,0:20:07.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know what happened 20 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.44,0:20:10.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but shouldn't you turn\Nyourself in, Sakata-han?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.74,0:20:15.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.58,0:20:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all over at this point...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.88,0:20:22.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.49,0:20:24.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sakata is the killer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.72,0:20:28.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right! Numabuchi told us everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.33,0:20:32.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he committed the murders,\Nhe planned to frame Numabuchi
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.66,0:20:36.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then kill him in a fake suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.73,0:20:38.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's Sakata?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.04,0:20:40.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-He's been gone awhile...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.65,0:20:52.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There, it's empty! Now you\Ncan't do anything stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.32,0:20:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A bullet hit your leg?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.86,0:21:03.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-Never mind me, Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...\NHurry and escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.39,0:21:09.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No can do... Looks like I got hit, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.83,0:21:16.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was my father...\NThe instructor who died 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.04,0:21:17.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was a strict driver
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.71,0:21:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and was always telling my\Nmother to check the rear-view mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.35,0:21:27.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's probably where I got it from.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.02,0:21:30.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think someone like\Nthat would drive drunk?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.76,0:21:34.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then I became a police detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.43,0:21:38.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...to expose the truth of my father's death!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.23,0:21:44.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I solved the mystery when I found\NNumabuchi in a mountain shack.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.07,0:21:49.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I look like my father, so the\Ninstant he saw me, he grew frightened
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.07,0:21:51.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and blurted everything out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.44,0:21:55.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,F-Forgive me, Instructor Inaba!\NIt was just a prank!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.75,0:21:58.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just wanted to see your scared face
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.75,0:22:03.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when we forced you to drink and\Ndrive a car without brake fluid!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.82,0:22:09.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then you went after all\Nsix people who took part in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.96,0:22:13.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The statute of limitations\Nfor murder is 15 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.16,0:22:18.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I decided that if the law\Ncan't punish them, I would!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.01,0:22:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry I dragged you into this, Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.91,0:22:31.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Don't talk like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.62,0:22:39.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're a cop! You're the only ones\Nin Japan allowed to carry guns!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.09,0:22:43.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't you feel any pride for that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.29,0:22:45.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get up, Sakata!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.70,0:22:50.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You put the cherry blossom\Nemblem on your notebook to shame!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.08,0:23:07.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Otaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.22,0:23:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How's Heiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.49,0:23:12.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They took him away in\Nanother ambulance just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.52,0:23:18.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's really something. He carried\Nyou out of that fire, on his back.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.83,0:23:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.73,0:23:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this the homicidal\Nmaniac who tried to kill me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.67,0:23:25.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why, you...!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.87,0:23:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He is still my subordinate. Hands off.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.78,0:23:35.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Old man Toyama!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.98,0:23:40.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll pay a visit later, Goshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.45,0:23:45.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I do, we can talk about\Nwhat happened 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.75,0:24:19.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to do something else\Ndangerous, like stand on ice
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.02,0:24:25.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I also want to realize\Nthe dreams I came up with
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.83,0:24:29.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forever my destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.07,0:24:36.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If a spaceship landed\Nright before my very eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.11,0:24:43.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure I would leave my\Nfriends behind and leave Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.32,0:24:53.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said having uneventful\Nday after day is the best
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.22,0:24:57.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I'm really Just running away,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.46,0:25:03.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,unable to keep up with days without you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.43,0:25:11.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like standing on ice, it's a secret
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.74,0:25:18.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if I loved you, my heart would\Nfly off even faster than light
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.62,0:25:22.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forever my destiny
